OL,3,CBBC must take quicker action when
OL,4,Cstaff step out of line, report says
OL,6,FThe review, led by management
OL,7,Fconsultant Grahame Russell, was
OL,8,Flaunched in the wake of the furore
OL,9,Fover disgraced former newsreader Huw
OL,10,FEdwards and is understood to rule out
OL,11,Fthe presence of a toxic culture but
OL,12,Ffound that improvements can be made.
OL,14,FIt is believed the review, on
OL,15,F"preventing abuse of power and
OL,16,Fensuring everyone at the BBC conducts
OL,17,Fthemselves in line" with its values,
OL,18,Fwill also set out what the corporation
OL,19,Fexpects from staff.
