OL,6,FEarlier this year, a BBC review found
OL,7,Fa number of people "felt unable to
OL,8,Fraise" concerns about Russell Brand
OL,9,Fwhen he was a radio presenter at the
OL,10,Fcorporation.
OL,12,FThe BBC Board also apologised in
OL,13,FJanuary after a review found it "did
OL,14,Fnot take adequate action" upon
OL,15,Flearning about concerns regarding the
OL,16,Fbehaviour of veteran DJ Tim Westwood.
OL,18,FComedian and actor Brand, and ex-BBC
OL,19,FRadio 1 presenter Westwood, both deny
OL,20,Fany wrongdoing or inappropriate
OL,21,Fbehaviour.
